f3ErpMIB.name: f3ErpMIB

revisions.description: Notes from release 201209130000Z, (1)MIB version ready for release FSP150CC 5.6CC.

f3ErpMIB.contactinfo: Jakub Zalewski ADVA Optical Networking, Inc. Tel: +48 58 7716 411 E-mail: jzalewski@advaoptical.com Postal: ul. Slaska 35/37 81-310 Gdynia, Poland
f3ErpMIB.description: This module defines the G.8032 Ethernet Ring Protection MIB definitions used by the F3 (FSP150CM/CC) product lines. Copyright (C) ADVA Optical Networking.

ERPGroupAction.name: ERPGroupAction
ERPGroupAction.description: User action initiated on ERP group

RapsInterconnectionNode.name: RapsInterconnectionNode
RapsInterconnectionNode.description: Role of the sub-ring interconnection node

RapsMultipleFailure.name: RapsMultipleFailure
RapsMultipleFailure.description: Indicates the interconnection node that has to perform the Manual Switch for minimizing interconnected ring segmentation

f3ErpGroupTable.name: f3ErpGroupTable
f3ErpGroupTable.description: A list of entries corresponding to Ethernet Ring Protection instance for configuration purposes.

f3ErpGroupEntry.name: f3ErpGroupEntry
f3ErpGroupEntry.description: A conceptual row in the f3ErpGroupTable.

f3ErpGroupIndex.name: f3ErpGroupIndex
f3ErpGroupIndex.description: An integer index value used to uniquely identify this ERP Group within Network Element.

f3ErpGroupAdminState.name: f3ErpGroupAdminState
f3ErpGroupAdminState.description: Administrative State of this ERP instance. INSERVICE is normal operation. MANAGEMENT suppresses alarms. DISABLED initiates blocking on ring port 0 and stops all RAPS processing and forwarding. The ERP instance must be in the MANAGEMENT or DISABLED state when modifying the following ERP instance attributes: rapsVID, ringPort0, ringPort1, ringPort0RPLRole, ringPort1RPLRole, rapsRingId, rapsMdLevel, subRingWithoutVirtualChannel, compatibleVersion.

f3ErpGroupOperationalState.name: f3ErpGroupOperationalState
f3ErpGroupOperationalState.description: Operational State of this ERP instance. The ERP operational state is outage when there is an equipment failure causing the ERP to be non-functional; otherwise the operational state is normal.

f3ErpGroupSecondaryState.name: f3ErpGroupSecondaryState
f3ErpGroupSecondaryState.description: Secondary State of this ERP instance. The ERP secondary state is supporting entity outage (SGEO) when there is an equipment failure causing the ERP to be non-functional; otherwise the sescondary state is active.

f3ErpGroupRapsRingId.name: f3ErpGroupRapsRingId
f3ErpGroupRapsRingId.description: Ring ID of this ERP instance. The value is used in the destination address of the RAPS PDU.

f3ErpGroupRapsNodeId.name: f3ErpGroupRapsNodeId
f3ErpGroupRapsNodeId.description: Node ID of the local system for this ERP instance. The value is used as the Node ID in the RAPS PDU.

f3ErpGroupRapsVlanId.name: f3ErpGroupRapsVlanId
f3ErpGroupRapsVlanId.description: VID value of the VLAN tag for transmitted/received RAPS PDUs for this ERP instance.

f3ErpGroupRapsVlanPrio.name: f3ErpGroupRapsVlanPrio
f3ErpGroupRapsVlanPrio.description: P-bit value of the VLAN tag for transmitted RAPS PDUs for this ERP instance.

f3ErpGroupRapsVlanEtherType.name: f3ErpGroupRapsVlanEtherType
f3ErpGroupRapsVlanEtherType.description: VID value of the VLAN tag for transmitted/received RAPS PDUs for this ERP instance.

f3ErpGroupRapsMdLevel.name: f3ErpGroupRapsMdLevel
f3ErpGroupRapsMdLevel.description: MD (or MEG) level of the transmitted/received RAPS PDUs for this ERP instance.

f3ErpGroupCompatibleVersion.name: f3ErpGroupCompatibleVersion
f3ErpGroupCompatibleVersion.description: Indicates compatability with a version of G.8032 for this ring instance.

f3ErpGroupRevertive.name: f3ErpGroupRevertive
f3ErpGroupRevertive.description: Revertive control for the ring. Only applicable on the RPL Owner node.

f3ErpGroupSubRingWithoutVirtChan.name: f3ErpGroupSubRingWithoutVirtChan
f3ErpGroupSubRingWithoutVirtChan.description: Indicates whether R-APS channel forms a closed loop around the ring ENABLED: no RAPS Virtual Channel (i.e., open ring) DISABLED: RAPS forms a closed loop (major ring or sub-ring with virtual channel)

f3ErpGroupGuardTime.name: f3ErpGroupGuardTime
f3ErpGroupGuardTime.description: The Guard Time value in milliseconds for this ERP instance.

f3ErpGroupWaitToRestore.name: f3ErpGroupWaitToRestore
f3ErpGroupWaitToRestore.description: The Wait-to-Restore time value in minutes for this ERP instance.

f3ErpGroupHoldOffTime.name: f3ErpGroupHoldOffTime
f3ErpGroupHoldOffTime.description: The Hold-off Time value in milliseconds for this ERP instance.

f3ErpGroupRingPort0.name: f3ErpGroupRingPort0
f3ErpGroupRingPort0.description: Pointer to a Port instance which represents Ring Port 0 in the ERP Group. The pointer must be set to cmEthernetAccPortIndex instance if the Ring Port is an Access Port or to cmEthernetNetPortIndex if the Ring Port is a Network Port.

f3ErpGroupRingPort0MEP.name: f3ErpGroupRingPort0MEP
f3ErpGroupRingPort0MEP.description: Pointer to a CFM MEP instance monitoring Ring Port 0 for this ERP instance. The pointer must be set to dot1agCfmMepIfIndex instance.

f3ErpGroupRingPort0Role.name: f3ErpGroupRingPort0Role
f3ErpGroupRingPort0Role.description: RPL Role of Ring Port 0. When f3ErpGroupRingPort1Role is NEIGHBOR or OWNER, this value MUST be NONE.

f3ErpGroupRingPort1.name: f3ErpGroupRingPort1
f3ErpGroupRingPort1.description: Pointer to a Port instance which represents Ring Port 1 in the ERP Group. The pointer must be set to cmEthernetAccPortIndex instance if the Ring Port is an Access Port or to cmEthernetNetPortIndex if the Ring Port is a Network Port.

f3ErpGroupRingPort1MEP.name: f3ErpGroupRingPort1MEP
f3ErpGroupRingPort1MEP.description: Pointer to a CFM MEP instance monitoring Ring Port 1 for this ERP instance. The pointer must be set to dot1agCfmMepIfIndex instance.

f3ErpGroupRingPort1Role.name: f3ErpGroupRingPort1Role
f3ErpGroupRingPort1Role.description: RPL Role of Ring Port 1. When f3ErpGroupRingPort0Role is NEIGHBOR or OWNER, this value MUST be NONE.

f3ErpGroupProtectMgmtTunnel.name: f3ErpGroupProtectMgmtTunnel
f3ErpGroupProtectMgmtTunnel.description: Indication of whether this ERP instance is protecting management Tunnels on the ring ports.

f3ErpGroupWTRRemainingTime.name: f3ErpGroupWTRRemainingTime
f3ErpGroupWTRRemainingTime.description: The time remaining (in seconds) for this ERP instance to wait to restore.

f3ErpGroupTxRapsRequest.name: f3ErpGroupTxRapsRequest
f3ErpGroupTxRapsRequest.description: Request/State field fo the last generated R-APS message on the Ring Ports. Valid when the node is blocking.

f3ErpGroupTxRapsRplBlocked.name: f3ErpGroupTxRapsRplBlocked
f3ErpGroupTxRapsRplBlocked.description: RPL Blocked field fo the last generated R-APS message on the Ring Ports. Valid when the node is blocking.

f3ErpGroupTxRapsDNF.name: f3ErpGroupTxRapsDNF
f3ErpGroupTxRapsDNF.description: Do Not Flush field fo the last generated R-APS message on the Ring Ports. Valid when the node is blocking.

f3ErpGroupTxRapsBPR.name: f3ErpGroupTxRapsBPR
f3ErpGroupTxRapsBPR.description: Blocked Port Reference field fo the last generated R-APS message on the Ring Ports. Valid when the node is blocking.

f3ErpGroupAction.name: f3ErpGroupAction
f3ErpGroupAction.description: User action performed on this ERP instance. For manualSwitch and forcedSwitch actions f3ErpGroupActionObject has to be specified prior to settng this object.

f3ErpGroupActionObject.name: f3ErpGroupActionObject
f3ErpGroupActionObject.description: Object identfier used to specify the OID of a port on which f3ErpGroupAction should occur. Applicable for manualSwitch and forcedSwitch actions. The pointer must be set to cmEthernetAccPortIndex instance if the Ring Port is an Access Port or to cmEthernetNetPortIndex if the Ring Port a Network Port.

f3ErpGroupUserLabel.name: f3ErpGroupUserLabel
f3ErpGroupUserLabel.description: User Label associated with the ERP Group.

f3ErpGroupStorageType.name: f3ErpGroupStorageType
f3ErpGroupStorageType.description: The type of storage configured for this entry.

f3ErpGroupRowStatus.name: f3ErpGroupRowStatus
f3ErpGroupRowStatus.description: The status of this row. An entry MUST NOT exist in the active state unless all objects in the entry have an appropriate value, as described in the description clause for each writable object. The values of f3ErpGroupRowStatus supported are createAndGo(4) and destroy(6). All mandatory attributes must be specified in a single SNMP SET request with neRowStatus value as createAndGo(4). Upon successful row creation, this object has a value of active(1). The f3ErpGroupRowStatus object may be modified if the associated instance of this object is equal to active(1).

f3ErpGroupInterconnectionErp.name: f3ErpGroupInterconnectionErp
f3ErpGroupInterconnectionErp.description: Oid of the associated Loop Avoidance instance at an interconnect node. Current only ERP instances are supported for this; in the future, STP instances may be as well.

f3ErpGroupInterconnectPropagateTc.name: f3ErpGroupInterconnectPropagateTc
f3ErpGroupInterconnectPropagateTc.description: Allows for propgation of Topology Change information in the protocol of the associated Loop Avoidance instance at an interconnect node. Derived from MI_RAPS_Propagate_TC in [G8032]

f3ErpGroupRapsVirtualChannelMep.name: f3ErpGroupRapsVirtualChannelMep
f3ErpGroupRapsVirtualChannelMep.description: ID of MEP monitoring an UP MEP Monitoring the R-APS VID.

f3ErpGroupMaxFpNum.name: f3ErpGroupMaxFpNum
f3ErpGroupMaxFpNum.description: The max number of flow point which the erp supports. This object is not supported - setting its value will not have any effect on the System.

f3ErpGroupRapsInterconnectionNode.name: f3ErpGroupRapsInterconnectionNode
f3ErpGroupRapsInterconnectionNode.description: Type of sub-ring interconnection node. PRIMARY/SECONDARY role for minimizing interconnected ring segmentation.

f3ErpGroupRapsMultipleFailure.name: f3ErpGroupRapsMultipleFailure
f3ErpGroupRapsMultipleFailure.description: Sub-ring interconnection node that is designated to perform the Manual Switch for minimizing interconnected ring segmentation.

f3ErpGroupProtectedFlowTable.name: f3ErpGroupProtectedFlowTable
f3ErpGroupProtectedFlowTable.description: A list of entries corresponding to Flows which are protected by an ERP group instance. These flows can be access flows or multipoint flows depending on the traffic model of the ERP Ring Port.

f3ErpGroupProtectedFlowEntry.name: f3ErpGroupProtectedFlowEntry
f3ErpGroupProtectedFlowEntry.description: A conceptual row in the f3ErpGroupProtectedFlowsTable.

f3ErpGroupProtectedFlow.name: f3ErpGroupProtectedFlow
f3ErpGroupProtectedFlow.description: Pointer to a Flow instance which is protected by an ERP instance. The pointer must be set to cmFlowIndex or cmMPFlowIndex instance.

f3ErpUnitTable.name: f3ErpUnitTable
f3ErpUnitTable.description: A list of entries corresponding to Ethernet Ring Protection Unit

f3ErpUnitEntry.name: f3ErpUnitEntry
f3ErpUnitEntry.description: A conceptual row in the f3ErpUnitTable.

f3ErpUnitIndex.name: f3ErpUnitIndex
f3ErpUnitIndex.description: An integer index value used to uniquely identify this ERP Unit within ERP Group.

f3ErpUnitPort.name: f3ErpUnitPort
f3ErpUnitPort.description: ERP Unit's points to a facility (port). This object represents the facility Network Element port.

f3ErpUnitPortMEP.name: f3ErpUnitPortMEP
f3ErpUnitPortMEP.description: Pointer to a CFM MEP instance monitoring Ring Port.

f3ErpUnitPortRole.name: f3ErpUnitPortRole
f3ErpUnitPortRole.description: RPL Role of Ring Port 1. When f3ErpGroupRingPort2Role is NEIGHBOR or OWNER, this value MUST be NONE.

f3ErpUnitPortRxRapsRequest.name: f3ErpUnitPortRxRapsRequest
f3ErpUnitPortRxRapsRequest.description: Request/State field fo the last received R-APS message on Ring Port.

f3ErpUnitPortRxRapsRplBlocked.name: f3ErpUnitPortRxRapsRplBlocked
f3ErpUnitPortRxRapsRplBlocked.description: RPL Blocked field fo the last received R-APS message on Ring Port.

f3ErpUnitPortRxRapsDNF.name: f3ErpUnitPortRxRapsDNF
f3ErpUnitPortRxRapsDNF.description: Do Not Flush field fo the last received R-APS message on Ring Port.

f3ErpUnitPortRxRapsBPR.name: f3ErpUnitPortRxRapsBPR
f3ErpUnitPortRxRapsBPR.description: Blocked Port Reference field fo the last received R-APS message on Ring Port.

f3ErpUnitPortRxRapsNodeId.name: f3ErpUnitPortRxRapsNodeId
f3ErpUnitPortRxRapsNodeId.description: Node ID of the local system for this ERP instance. The value is used as the Node ID in the RAPS PDU.

f3ErpUnitPortRapsFp.name: f3ErpUnitPortRapsFp
f3ErpUnitPortRapsFp.description: Pointer to a R-APS FlowPoint associated with this Ring Port.

f3ErpUnitStatsTable.name: f3ErpUnitStatsTable
f3ErpUnitStatsTable.description: A list of entries corresponding to Ethernet Ring Protection Unit Statistics

f3ErpUnitStatsEntry.name: f3ErpUnitStatsEntry
f3ErpUnitStatsEntry.description: A conceptual row in the f3ErpUnitStatsTable.

f3ErpUnitNumBlockedStateTrans.name: f3ErpUnitNumBlockedStateTrans
f3ErpUnitNumBlockedStateTrans.description: Total number of transitions into a blocking state for Ring Port.

f3ErpUnitRapsPDUsTx.name: f3ErpUnitRapsPDUsTx
f3ErpUnitRapsPDUsTx.description: Count of all RAPS PDUs transmitted on the port where the PDU contains the MEG Level, Ring ID and VID for the ERP instance.

f3ErpUnitRapsPDUsRx.name: f3ErpUnitRapsPDUsRx
f3ErpUnitRapsPDUsRx.description: Count of all RAPS PDUs received on the port where the PDU contains the MEG Level, Ring ID and VID for the ERP instance.

f3ErpUnitRapsPDUsDiscarded.name: f3ErpUnitRapsPDUsDiscarded
f3ErpUnitRapsPDUsDiscarded.description: Count of all RAPS PDUs received on the port and discarded where the PDU contains the MEG Level, Ring ID and VID for the ERP instance.

f3ErpUnitRapsNoReqPDUsTx.name: f3ErpUnitRapsNoReqPDUsTx
f3ErpUnitRapsNoReqPDUsTx.description: Count of No Request RAPS PDUs transmitted on the port where the PDU contains the MEG Level, Ring ID and VID for the ERP instance.

f3ErpUnitRapsNoReqRBPDUsTx.name: f3ErpUnitRapsNoReqRBPDUsTx
f3ErpUnitRapsNoReqRBPDUsTx.description: Count of No Request, RPL Blocked RAPS PDUs transmitted on the port where the PDU contains the MEG Level, Ring ID and VID for the ERP instance.

f3ErpUnitRapsSignalFailPDUsTx.name: f3ErpUnitRapsSignalFailPDUsTx
f3ErpUnitRapsSignalFailPDUsTx.description: Count of Signal Fail RAPS PDUs transmitted on the port where the PDU contains the MEG Level, Ring ID and VID for the ERP instance.

f3ErpUnitRapsManualSwitchPDUsTx.name: f3ErpUnitRapsManualSwitchPDUsTx
f3ErpUnitRapsManualSwitchPDUsTx.description: Count of Manual Switch RAPS PDUs transmitted on the port where the PDU contains the MEG Level, Ring ID and VID for the ERP instance.

f3ErpUnitRapsForcedSwitchPDUsTx.name: f3ErpUnitRapsForcedSwitchPDUsTx
f3ErpUnitRapsForcedSwitchPDUsTx.description: Count of Forced Switch RAPS PDUs transmitted on the port where the PDU contains the MEG Level, Ring ID and VID for the ERP instance.

f3ErpUnitRapsEventPDUsTx.name: f3ErpUnitRapsEventPDUsTx
f3ErpUnitRapsEventPDUsTx.description: Count of Event RAPS PDUs transmitted on the port where the PDU contains the MEG Level, Ring ID and VID for the ERP instance.

f3ErpUnitRapsNoReqPDUsRx.name: f3ErpUnitRapsNoReqPDUsRx
f3ErpUnitRapsNoReqPDUsRx.description: Count of No Request RAPS PDUs received on the port where the PDU contains the MEG Level, Ring ID and VID for the ERP instance.

f3ErpUnitRapsNoReqRBPDUsRx.name: f3ErpUnitRapsNoReqRBPDUsRx
f3ErpUnitRapsNoReqRBPDUsRx.description: Count of No Request, RPL Blocked RAPS PDUs received on the port where the PDU contains the MEG Level, Ring ID and VID for the ERP instance.

f3ErpUnitRapsSignalFailPDUsRx.name: f3ErpUnitRapsSignalFailPDUsRx
f3ErpUnitRapsSignalFailPDUsRx.description: Count of Signal Fail RAPS PDUs received on the port where the PDU contains the MEG Level, Ring ID and VID for the ERP instance.

f3ErpUnitRapsManualSwitchPDUsRx.name: f3ErpUnitRapsManualSwitchPDUsRx
f3ErpUnitRapsManualSwitchPDUsRx.description: Count of Manual Switch RAPS PDUs received on the port where the PDU contains the MEG Level, Ring ID and VID for the ERP instance.

f3ErpUnitRapsForcedSwitchPDUsRx.name: f3ErpUnitRapsForcedSwitchPDUsRx
f3ErpUnitRapsForcedSwitchPDUsRx.description: Count of Forced Switch RAPS PDUs received on the port where the PDU contains the MEG Level, Ring ID and VID for the ERP instance.

f3ErpUnitRapsEventPDUsRx.name: f3ErpUnitRapsEventPDUsRx
f3ErpUnitRapsEventPDUsRx.description: Count of Event RAPS PDUs received on the port where the PDU contains the MEG Level, Ring ID and VID for the ERP instance.

f3ErpUnitRapsInvalidOamVersionPDUsRx.name: f3ErpUnitRapsInvalidOamVersionPDUsRx
f3ErpUnitRapsInvalidOamVersionPDUsRx.description: Count of OAM PDUs received on the port where the PDU contains the MEG Level, Ring ID and VID for the ERP instance and an OAM Version field other than 0 or 1.

f3ErpUnitRapsRsvdRequestPDUsRx.name: f3ErpUnitRapsRsvdRequestPDUsRx
f3ErpUnitRapsRsvdRequestPDUsRx.description: Count of OAM PDUs received on the port where the PDU contains the MEG Level, Ring ID and VID for the ERP instance.

f3ErpUnitRapsRsvdEventSubcode.name: f3ErpUnitRapsRsvdEventSubcode
f3ErpUnitRapsRsvdEventSubcode.description: Count of OAM PDUs received on the port where the PDU contains the MEG Level, Ring ID and VID for the ERP instance, an OAM Opcode field of 40 (R-APS), a request/state value of 14 (EVT) and a sub-code value that is not 0.
